  "text": "To further characterize potential reactivation of HIV-1 by SJ23B, Rullas et al. [CITATION_1] transfected primary resting T-lymphocytes with either a full-length provirus, LTR or luciferase expression vectors under the control of consensus sequences for NF-κB, Sp1 and NF-AT transcription factors. These experiments showed that SJ23B activates transcription through activation of NF-κB and Sp1 in these cells.",
